# SMS Messaging

Send and receive SMS and MMS messages through the Twilio Messaging API. Messages are delivered globally via Twilio's carrier network from a purchased phone number or Messaging Service.

## Sending an SMS

```javascript
const twilio = require("twilio");

const client = twilio(
  process.env.TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID,
  process.env.TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN
);

const message = await client.messages.create({
  to: "+15551234567",
  from: process.env.TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER,
  body: "Hello from Twilio!",
});

console.log(message.sid); // SM...
console.log(message.status); // "queued"
```

## Receiving SMS

Configure a webhook URL in the Twilio Console (Phone Numbers > Active Numbers > Messaging). When an SMS arrives, Twilio sends a POST request with `From`, `To`, `Body`, and other fields. Respond with TwiML to reply (see [[twilio/twiml#messaging-verbs]]).

```javascript
const express = require("express");
const { MessagingResponse } = require("twilio").twiml;

const app = express();
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: false }));

app.post("/sms", (req, res) => {
  const twiml = new MessagingResponse();
  twiml.message(`You said: ${req.body.Body}`);
  res.type("text/xml").send(twiml.toString());
});
```

## MMS Media

Send images, GIFs, and other media by including a `mediaUrl` array:

```javascript
const message = await client.messages.create({
  to: "+15551234567",
  from: process.env.TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER,
  body: "Check out this image!",
  mediaUrl: ["https://example.com/image.jpg"],
});
```

MMS is supported on US and Canadian numbers. International numbers fall back to SMS with a link.

## Status Callbacks

Track delivery status by providing a `statusCallback` URL:

```javascript
const message = await client.messages.create({
  to: "+15551234567",
  from: process.env.TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER,
  body: "Tracked message",
  statusCallback: "https://example.com/status",
});
```

Twilio sends POST requests as the message progresses: `queued` > `sent` > `delivered` (or `failed` / `undelivered`).

## Messaging Services

For high-volume sending, use a Messaging Service instead of a single number. A Messaging Service pools multiple phone numbers, handles opt-out compliance, and provides intelligent sender selection:

```javascript
const message = await client.messages.create({
  to: "+15551234567",
  messagingServiceSid: "MG...",
  body: "Sent via Messaging Service",
});
```
